\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs26\b0 In a poignant scene set against the backdrop of a stormy Chicago skyline, Evan Vaughn grapples with the finalization of his divorce, haunted by a childhood vow never to follow in his parents' footsteps. Amidst the solemn atmosphere of Sarah's attorneys' office, Evan confronts his emotions and the stark contrast between his and Sarah's legal representation. His attention shifts from the attorneys' debate, perceived as mere theatrics, to his sister Liz's supportive presence, and finally to Sarah, whose changed appearance evokes memories of their initial, magical connection. Evan's internal struggle is palpable as he silently seeks a sign of their once-shared love, leaving him adrift in his own turmoil and unanswered questions.}{ }}